blurb:
#NoEstamosAquídeVisita Publicaremos las nuevas novelas gráficas de nuestros autores:

Logan Wayne, H.G. Santarriaga y Tebin.
name: 3 Novelas Gráficas Mexicanas de Pura Pinche Fortaleza Cómics
story:
['Story
Nosotros somos Pura Pinche Fortaleza Cómics y desde 2018, gracias al apoyo de muchos lectores solidarios, No estamos aquí de visita.
Hemos hecho dos campañas exitosas, la que trajo a la vida la antología del maestro Ricardo Peláez "Fuego Lento" y la de este año, al publicar la espectacular edición de "Operación Bolívar" del maestro Edgar Clement.
Ahora estamos lanzando esta nueva campaña trayendo las 3 nuevas novelas gráficas de nuestros autores Tebin, Logan Wayne y H.G. Santarriaga.
Rota ¿Cómo superar el duelo y Ruptura? Esta \xa0es la alegoría de un grupo de corazones rotos y abandonados,\xa0cayendo en \xa0lo más profundo de su dolor.\xa0 Juntos vivirán una conmovedora historia metafórica de superación a través de símbolos y mensajes... Rota es la nueva novela gráfica de 64 páginas de Esteban Saldaña, TEBIN y es parte de este triple lanzamiento del que esperamos seas parte del mismo.
Las Malas Lenguas es la cuarta novela gráfica de Logan Wayne, una vez más acompañado por la gráfica del artista Luis Erre. Todo mundo va a decir cosas de ella, las malas lenguas te dirán que se trata de una historia triste derivada del temblor del 2017, otros te dirán que es una historia del reencuentro de un hombre viejo y amargado con su hija fracasada, otros te dirán que es un catálogo de instrucciones de esos juegos a los que jugábamos cuando éramos niños y algunos más dirán que es una historia de redención, muerte y esperanza con una pizca de filosofía propia de la obra de Logan Wayne. Las Malas lenguas es una novela gráfica de 96 páginas que está urgida por que la devores con los ojos y con el corazón.
Sueños Rotos: Emi es la tercera parte de la trilogía Sueños Rotos, Primero fue la inquietante historia de Sofía. Después la desgarradora y contundente Julia y ahora llega Emi a cerrar este ciclo en el que se pone en un cómic el asunto tan delicado de la trata de personas.\xa0
H.G. Santarriaga nos trae una novela gráfica de 96 páginas en las que conocemos la historia de EMI y después de esto estamos seguros que algo en tu interior jamás será igual.
La ausencia de eventos, debido a la pandemia nos motivó a hacer estas dinámicas de fondeo de proyectos, para obtener los recursos y así seguir publicando, \xa0sin embargo, ahora es también una buena herramienta para que tú, que estás leyendo esto y los demás lectores solidarios tengan nuestros nuevos lanzamientos a un precio extremadamente accesible, con unas recompensas bien nutridas y con la calidad y seriedad que te mereces y nos caracteriza.
Los fondos \xa0serán útiles para hacer todo el proceso editorial hasta \xa0culminar en a la publicación de las 3 obras, mismas que ya están prácticamente terminadas.
We are Pura Pinche Fortaleza Cómics and since 2018, thanks to the support of many supportive readers, we are not visiting here. We have carried out two successful campaigns, the one that brought to life the anthology of maestro Ricardo Peláez "Fuego Lento" and this year's, by publishing the spectacular edition of "Operación Bolívar" by maestro Edgar Clement. We are now launching this new campaign bringing the 3 new graphic novels from our authors Tebin, Logan Wayne and H.G. Santarriaga. Broken How to overcome grief and Breakup? This is the allegory of a group of broken and abandoned hearts, falling into the depths of their pain. Together they will live a moving metaphorical story of overcoming through symbols and messages... Rota is the new 64-page graphic novel by Esteban Saldaña, TEBIN, and is part of this triple release that we hope you will be a part of. Las Malas Lenguas is Logan Wayne's fourth graphic novel, once again accompanied by graphic artist Luis Erre. Everyone is going to say things about her, gossips will tell you that it is a sad story derived from the 2017 earthquake, others will tell you that it is a story of the reunion of an old and bitter man with his failed daughter, others will tell you which is a catalog of instructions for those games we played when we were kids and some others will say that it is a story of redemption, death and hope with a pinch of philosophy typical of the work of Logan Wayne. Las Malas Lenguas is a 96-page graphic novel that is urgently needed for you to devour it with your eyes and with your heart. Broken Dreams: Emi is the third part of the Broken Dreams trilogy, First it was the disturbing story of Sofia. Then the heartbreaking and forceful Julia and now Emi arrives to close this cycle in which the delicate issue of human trafficking is put into a comic. H.G. Santarriaga brings us a 96-page graphic novel in which we learn about the history of EMI and after this we are sure that something inside you will never be the same. The absence of events, due to the pandemic, motivated us to do these project funding dynamics, to obtain the resources and thus continue publishing, however, now it is also a good tool for you, who are reading this and the other readers. solidarity have our new releases at an extremely affordable price, with well-nourished rewards and with the quality and seriousness that you deserve and that characterizes us. The funds will be used to carry out the entire editorial process until the publication of the 3 works, which are practically finished.
A continuación Las Recompensas:








































































































Operación Bolívar y Fuego Lento SC








Operación Bolívar y Fuego Lento Firmados con sus copias digitales y Agradecimiento en los tres libros.
































































































Los libros que puedes elegir .']

blurb: The Floasis is a flow and circus arts space that offers classes, shows, community events, and props for new spinners. Help us improve!
name: Help Improve the Floasis!
story:
['StoryHelp us improve the Floasis!Who are we and what do we do?The Floasis is a movement space dedicated to the practice and teaching of flow, circus, and martial arts. We also open the NYC
flow arts community to guest teachers, and provide a space where students can learn, practice, and perform. We give
students the space and resources necessary to develop their skills or even become professionals in their chosen arts. We also foster a
sense of community among NYC flow arts performers!Want to meet us? \xa0Come to a spin jam! \xa0Click the picture below to see our upcoming community events.


Join us for a spin jam!





Our skill share events attract a diverse group of artists and performers. \xa0Want to learn something new or improve on what you know?How about hula hoop?


Ali Luminescent at a Floasis Flow Market






\xa0Staff?


Krisstina Hawks at the Floasis






Or all kinds of circus arts?


Catch Tara on the road at festivals for fire classes!








Catch Tara on the road at festivals for fire classes!





\xa0The Floasis draws artists and teachers with all kinds of skills: hula hoop, staff, fans, double staves, dragon staff, rope dart, poi, juggling, stilt walking, side show arts, and more! We're an awesome place to meet teachers or artists interested in skill-share!What do we give back?We're an awesome community center for flow artists in NYC and beyond! \xa0We offer classes, events like flow markets and variety shows, rehearsal space, and free community events like spin jams.Our kickstarter-funded renovations will allow us to open a gift shop so we can sell merchandise from prop makers and flow artists from all over country, and the world! \xa0We'll also be offering artist residencies at the Floasis so out-of-town artists have an affordable place to stay and teach in NYC. \xa0Help us finish making this happen!We also help new and experienced artists and performers by offering a community center and a place to develop new material, test it with an audience, and rehearse. \xa0We're working to help keep our neighborhood and the city interesting and artistic!\xa0

What are we working on?We're working on a number of projects this year to help us expand as a center for community and education in NYC. \xa0Our skill-share and practice events are donation-based, and our events are inexpensive. \xa0Help us keep them that way while we improve our indoor dance studio, improve the backyard event space, and acquire the space next door!


Yardwork is super fun! :D





What do we need and why do we need it?


Where will your money go?





Outdoor renovations: $1000This year we've made a lot of renovations to our outdoor space including a covered audience area, new infrastructure to accommodate more people at events, and we've started replacing old and weather damaged equipment. \xa0We need: Safety signage, audience barriers, increased seating, and more infrastructure for weather protection.Indoor and basement studio renovations and expansion: $4200We've been busy in the basement! \xa0So far we've gutted the space, reorganized and repainted, installed LED lighting and wood laminate flooring, and started raising the ceiling to allow for more spin space. \xa0We've also opened negotiations to acquire more space next door!We need: an improved seating and audience area, a completed raised ceiling, shatter proof mirrors, and an administrative station and supplies to help us host more events and classes inside.Props and community supplies: $800We keep our skill-share and practice events inclusive and supported by donations— the Floasis has always offered a selection of props for students and new or curious spinners to try out. \xa0Over time these props are lost, broken, or simply wear out. \xa0You can help us continue to provide supplies for our community.We need: consumable supplies, and materials to make loaner props such as sock poi, practice fans, staves, and juggling equipment.Rewards!Last minute rewards! \xa0We have a few last minute rewards for our last 72 hours!


Charmander with dragon staff pin by Noel Yee!




Pokemon pins! \xa0Charmander with a dragon staff by Noel Yee. Pins are 1.5" tall. \xa0$25 donation!


Fan evolution DVD by Vulcan




A copy of the fan evolution DVD by the Vulcan! \xa0Level up your fan tech :) $30 donation.Here's a peek at some of the rewards we'll give you to thank you for helping us improve our space!Class time: \xa0Join us at the Floasis for classes with amazing teachers such as


The Silver Man, Dustin Hubel








Tara McManus









Torrie Ogilvie





\xa0\xa0and more! \xa0You can grab a 1 hour private lesson for a $60 donation!Props: Want to pick up a new prop or expand your collection? Support our space and pick up a new prop by Frank Hatsis and the Rope Dart Academy, Randy Kato, and more!


Sash Dart by Rope Dart Academy








Hoops by Randy Kato- check out his Etsy store for reward options!








Folding fans!





Floasis Gear:\xa0We also have some cool rewards made by Floasis artists!Floasis stickers! \xa0Great for water bottles and other gear:


Floasis stickers!





Pokemon prop stickers by Noel Yee, $20 donation:Wooden stickers featuring your choice of charmander with a dragon staff or psyduck with a contact juggling ball.


Pokemon prop stickers!





Handmade keychains, for a 15$ donation:


Keychains!





\xa0Floasis logo T-shirts, each handprinted by Connie Wang of Iconartisty, $35 donation.
Hoodies, also by Iconartistry!



Badass hoodies by Connie Wang!





\xa0Wick covers with the Floasis logo: $20 contribution for a pair!



A set of two wick covers!





Thanks for your help!
We've already done so much in the space this year. \xa0Thanks for helping us do even more!']

blurb: BILINGUAL Space horror thriller. Novela de ciencia ficción espacial tras la industrialización de la teleportación cuántica en Español
name: Paralelo: a Space quantum science fiction illustrated novel
story:
['Story







¡Meta Alcanzada!

Goal reached!

Artcover by Nekro XIII

Campaign will finish on the 23/1/23 at 23:23 GMT + 1 time! Only couple of days to go anf we are nearly there!! Read here the first two chapters in English to make up your mind and join the \xa0adventure before is too late! Do not let Solar Innovations get away with it!

Story, campaign and release / Historia del proyecto, la campaña y la publicación
Paralelo started as a project in 2012, while working at the European Astronaut Centre, and on Quantum Teleportation projects. I clearly remember the room I was in the moment I had an idea for a story. Then, I pulled all those references I liked (Dead Space, Resident Evil, Alien, Asimov, Tarantino, Murakami, Kitano, Vampire The Masquerade, etc.) to shape the world of Paralelo, and let the story unfold including the religion of Virtue, The Hive, Quantum Technology or Space Exploration.\xa0
The amazing illustrations from Nekro XIII, LAPAN and Agata Fiszer were commisioned as the final draft underway. They made me see I wanted more than just art for the book cover, but rather to release the novel as if it was a Comic: by several issues with cover illustrations providing the reader's imagination a peak on how the story would go on. This is also a way of hard scheduling deadlines to finish editing and releasing chapters, something those who are parents will understand. Additionally, I realised I was not going to be able to share the story with loads of people I had met in different countries through the years, and thus started the English translation process, double checked by the proof reading of a native speakers lot, led by my wife.
This campaign will allow me to:

  Edit and release the story by issues in both languages and to publish it in e-format
  Continue commissioning amazing illustrations to accompany each issue
  Edit and publish printed versions in both languages

As an stretch goal, an additional English version review may be performed by a professional book editor. Other goals may come later!
10 years, 250 pages and many and many reviews and proofreading later, I hope to publish it the way I'd like it done: with high-quality illustrations bringing the words to life, and in two languages to make it accessible to the friends I made all over the world these last years.
Thank you so much for helping making it happen!
Diego
(ESP)
Comencé con el proyecto de Paralelo en 2012, mientras tabajaba en el Centro Europeo de Astronautas y en proyectos de Teleportación Cuántica. Recuerdo la sala donde estaba cuando tuve la idea de la historia. Luego pensé en todas esas referencias que me gustaban (Dead Space, Resident Evil, Alien, Asimov, Tarantino, Murakami, Kitano, Vampiro La Mascarada, etc.) para darle forma e ir construyendo el universo del libro con la religión de la Virtud, el Airball, \xa0La Colmena, la tecnología cuántica o la exploración espacial.
Poco a poco, las ilustraciones de Nekro XIII, LAPAN y Agata Fiszer fueron dándole vida al concepto de publicación por fascículos, como si fuera un cómic, permitiéndole imaginar al lector lo que va a encontrarse en los párrafos siguientes. Ésto, también me permite ir cerrando la edición de capítulos a medida que avanza la publicación, algo que los que son padres entenderán. A su vez, me di cuenta de que si quiería compartir mi historia con gran parte de mis conocidos, debía traducirla al menos al inglés dado que no eran hispanoparlantes. Por tanto, comencé a traducir el texto an inglés, con la ayuda y revisión de nativos angloparlantes, liderados por mi mujer.
Apoyar a esta campaña permite:

  Editar y publicar la historia en dos idiomas, por fascículos como libro electrónico\xa0
  Continuar comisionando ilustraciones exclusivas para acompañar a cada volumen
  Su edición y publicación impresa en ambos idiomas

Como logro desbloqueable, de momento, sería posible una revisión adicional del texto por un editor inglés profesional. Otros están por venir...
Años más tarde, espero poder hacer realidad mi sueño de publicarla con el formato en el que deseo hacerlo: incluyendo ilustraciones y en dos idiomas para hacerla accessible a mis amigos de todo el mundo. Muchísimas gracias por ayudarme a poder hacerlo realidad.
Paralelo printed book versions / ediciones impresas de Paralelo

Thanks to your pledge, the final editing and printing of the book may be not just possible but in two languages and in two formats: soft cover featuring LAPAN's cover art, and hard cover with Nekro XIII's illustration bringing the story of Paralelo to life.
Gracias a tu mecenazgo, Paralelo no solo podra ser editado y publicado, sino que lo hará en dos idiomas y en dos formatos: tapa blanda con ilustracion de portada de LAPAN, y tapa dura con la de Nekro XIII dándole vida a la historia.




Soft Cover -by LAPAN- and Hard Cover -by Nekro XIII-book versions art / Arte de las portadas tapa blanda (por LAPAN) y tapa dura (por Nekro XIII)





Solar Innovations Officially Licensed G'old Goodies! / Merchandising oficial de Solar Innovations

Get them with your pledge, or as an add on! /Cosíguelos con tu mecenazgo, o añádelos como extras
T-shirts / Camisetas









Cool Paralelo T-shirts featuring Nekro XIII's art /Camiseta con la ilustración de Nekro XIII para la portada
Tote bags / Bolsas de tela
Tote cotton bag featuging S.I.'s logo and the slogan displayed at the entrance of Social Hall 2B on Titan´s colony on one side; on the other, either Nekro XIII's or LAPAN´s cover art work.
Bolsas de Tela de S.I. En un lado el logotipo y el eslogan mostrado al entrar en el Hall Social 2B de La Colonia de Titán, con la terminal de aeronaves y de teleportación; en el otro la ilustración de portada de Nekro XIII o la de LAPAN.

























Illustrations in High Resolution, digital and printed formats, and printed \xa0/ Ilustraciones en formato digital de Alta Resolución, y/o impresas
All comissioned illustrations - those finalised thus far plus those to be comissioned thanks to your pledge- in High Resolution digital and/or printed format
Todas las ilustraciones comisionadas (las que llevamos hasta ahora y las que serán psoibles gracias al patrocinio) en formato digital de alta resolución y/o impresas

















About the author / Sobre el autor

Now then! I am a Space Engineer who has lived in many different countries for work, related to the industrialisation of Quantum Telecommunication / Teleportation projects, the International Space Station, Satellite and Earth Observation Digital Platforms Operations. I was fascinated by the topic after learning of the Teleportation performed in Tenerife in 2012, for which you can find the link to ESA's on the picture below. This all, has heavily influenciated my already Sci-Fi / action \xa0/ rol populated mind, and helped me come up with a story I really enjoyed writing\xa0and seeing it unfold. I am now hoping and looking forward to sharing it with you.\xa0I hope you have a good time reading it.
¡Hola! Soy un ingeniero espacial que ha vivido en varios países, trabajando en proyectos como la industrializadion de la comunicación cuántica o demostraciones de teleportación, operaciones de satélites, plataformas de observación de la Tierra o la Estación Espacial Internacional. Descubrí el tema de la teleportación cuántica tras el experimento que tuvo lugar en Tenerife en 2012 - enlace a la noticia de la ESA en la foto de abajo-. Mi mente ya estaba fuertemente influenciada por la ciencia ficción y el rol, pero me fascinó tanto que hizo surgir una historia que disfruté mucho escribiendo y viendo como se desplegaba sola. Ahora, me gustaría compartirla contigo y espero que te guste y entretenga.




Credits @ESA





And below here you can spot me at work at the time I came up with the idea vs my current self creating this campaign. Cheers!
Aquí me tienen manos en la consola cuando comencé con el proyecto vs mi yo actual creando esta campaña :-)




How it started - how it´s going / Como empezó y como vamos













Rewards & Pledges / Recompensas y Mecenazgo

The available rewards are: book by e-issues, full e-book, illustrations in HR, illustrations card set, paperback printed version, hard cover printed version, goodies, \xa0and the possibility of publishing your art or short story (up to 3 pages and inspired by the book´s universe) on the Pledger's Annex.
The table below shows the rewards available with each version. Silco and Linium have the same rewards, paperback book in in English or Spanish. Same with Lagraña and Purity for the hard cover version. This seemed to be the best way to do it. Please note you can always personalize it with add-ons. Each version comes with an introduction to a main theme in the universe or Paralelo. I hope you enjoy reading trough them, and then... choose your weapon / version !
Las recompensas disponibles son las siguientes: libro por fascículos electrónicos, ilustraciones en Alta Resolución, ilustraciones impresas, libro impreso en tapa blanda, libro impreso en tapa dura, goodies, \xa0y la posibilidad de publicar tu arte o tu relato corto (de hasta 3 páginas e inspirado en el universo del libro) en el Anexo Mecenas.
La tabla siguiente lista las diferentes versiones y las recompensas atribuidas a cada una de ellas. Silco y Linium tienen las mismas recompensas, sólo que el libro en tapa blanda es en español o en inglés. Lo mismo pasa con las versiones Lagraña y Purity. Esta parecía ser la mejor forma de separar las versiones en ambos idiomas. Ten en cuenta que siempre puedes personalizar las recompensas con los complementos. Cada version incluye un pequeño comentario sobre algún pilar del mundo de Paralelo. Espero que disfrutes leyéndolos y adentrándote en la historia. ¡Elige tu arma / version!

























Titan
(ENG)
Discover the inside outs of Solar Innovation´s multiplanetary society and find out what is happening in Titan: there is much more than meets the eye on S.I.'s crown colony jewel.

Silco (impresión tapa blanda sólo en ESP)
El Silco es un mineral silicato mezcla de silicio, carbón fósil y aluminio encontrado en Titán y Europa cuyas propiedades posibilitaron la proliferación de aparatos cuánticos así como la teleportación humana.
Descubre la colonia minera de Titán y los entresijos de la sociedad interplanetaria creada por S.I. donde no es Silco todo lo que reluce... que se lo pregunten a Antonio.

Lagraña (impresión tapa dura en ESP)

Juan Lagraña es el fundador de Solar Innovations.
A continuación referimos un extracto del artículo publicado por el periodista Eduardo Ríos en la versión holográfica de El diario hoy:
"Marquen la fecha de ayer, 01 de abril de 2032 en la lista de aquellas a conmemorar [...] “Un pequeño paso para el hombre, un gran paso para la humanidad”, dijo en su día Neil Armstrong al pisar la superficie del satélite terrestre. En este caso debemos acuñar la frase, ¨un segundo para el hombre, una distancia inimaginable para la humanidad¨, pronunciada por un sonriente Juan Lagraña tras hacer que un reloj desapareciera de un extremo de una mesa y apareciera en el otro. Teleportación. No es ciencia ficción, es realidad y ocurrió ayer en Sevilla. Repetidas veces."
Las sombras del laboratorio bajo el desierto almeriense, los rumores de prubeas con sujetos, la desaparición de ciertos críticos, y del uso dado al poder obtenido gracias al monopolio multiplanetario serán desgranadas con esta edición.

The white marble fountain is the central landmark of the Park of Dawn in Panel 7, address [7,7,7] on the Matrix transborder and monorail system of the colony. It is a mandatory pilgrimage both for faithfuls of the Virtue as well as for tourists.

Aperito irradiance allows for revealing \xa0content hidden to the frequencies human eyes and brain understand. Get the full picture, dive into the hidden frecuencies, in both languages, and irradiate your knowledge showing off with goodies.

blurb: I am covering "Piggy" by NIN and I need help from YOU!! Help me fund the musician's, studio time and release of this song!!
name: Help JoeJoeKeys Cover Nine Inch Nails
story: ['StoryThe idea for this project wasn\'t even mine! It was my wife, Saria. She has had a vision of covering the Nine In Nails song "Piggy" for about 15 years now. One night a few weeks ago we decided to release something for our "Happy Hour Sessions" which is essentially us sitting around doing just that, having happy hour and singing songs. \xa0I woke up the morning after we recorded the intitial idea and I knew right away that this song had to be taken further. I researched the licensing and that costs $$. I also want to have a quality sounding recording and that also costs $$. Welcome, KICKSTARTER!!! I have always wanted to try this fundraising service and I am using this project to do so. \xa0I have figured out a budget for what I need to record and release this song. \xa0It is not terribly expensive but I figured, what better way to try out Kickstarter? So here goes. Please donate whatever you feel like is appropriate. \xa0I have listed the "rewards" for different levels of donations. I am not asking alot and the rewards are not much, but PLEASE help me get funding to release this song!! Thank you so much!! I am only writing music because of YOU, my fans.']

blurb: A political accessibility and accountability project for Albertans.
name: APAH - The Alberta Political Accountability Hub
story:
['StoryWant to try out the APAH? It's live now! Check it out at APAH.ca!

What is the Alberta Political Accountability Hub?
The APAH is an online service built to help Albertans hold their government accountable by bringing everything you need to know about Alberta's politics together in a single, easy-to-navigate website. Our primary focus is accessibility - it doesn't matter if you're busy, and it doesn't matter if you're super familiar with politics. Anyone can access the site and use it to benefit themselves.
Crucially, we are not an opinion service, nor are we a news organization. Think of us more along the lines of something like Wikipedia - come to us whenever you want to be able to quickly learn what exactly is happening with our government.\xa0

When is it going live?
The site will be going live ten days before the election, at midnight on April 7th!

What's on the site?
The APAH has five clearly defined, user-friendly categories for information:

Representatives









From here, you'll find everything you need to know about your MLA - a biography in both written and video form, some quick details about them, and information about what they've done in the Legislature. You can find their voting records, contact info, sponsored legislation, and affiliations through here.

Legislation









Are you tired of hearing an endless back and forth discussion on legislation that's just a "This government is ruining the economy!" "No, this government is saving the economy!" where you don't actually learn what the proposed legislation does? The APAH's Legislation section is designed to make it possible for the first time for Albertans to have access to the facts of the legislation, without commentary, presented in an easy-to-read format.

Committees









The committees section is going to tell you about when the committees are meeting, who the committee members are, what each specific committee does, and what committees in general do.

Parties









Here, you'll find everything you need to know about the parties of yesteryear and today. If you want to learn about the histories of these parties, we have crash course videos and written histories for you. If you want to learn how they stand on policies and stack up against one another, we have that information lined up too. If you want to know more about the leaders, we have that information for you - again, both in written and video form.

Elections









Search by riding or by party to find out who you want to support in the 2019 election, including access to their websites and social media. Voting is a complicated, frequently frustrating process of trying to determine who believes in what and who these people are, but with the APAH, all that information is just a couple clicks away.

Why did you make it?
Before the APAH, being politically informed meant one of two things - trying to search through a hedge maze of sites to find the single line or two of information that you needed, or else trying to sift through news stories and pick out the fact from the fiction. The Alberta Political Accountability Hub has all the information you need to know to be capable of making informed political decisions - and with an election right around the corner, that's never been more important.\xa0

And who exactly are you?
My name is Wyatt Tanton, and I'm a 20 year-old who was originally from Camrose (about an hour south-east of Edmonton), but I've moved around a lot over the years - Mill Bay on Vancouver Island, Warwick in Australia, and Montreal, in Quebec. I chose to start the first Political Accountability Hub in Alberta because I know that this is a province where people, regardless of their political leanings, just want to be able to make the decisions that are right for their family - and unfortunately, we've had decades of governments in this province who make it as hard as possible for us to figure out what's best for us. \xa0

Where can we find you?
Well, obviously, there's APAH.ca - this is the main site for our service. However, we will also have Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram accounts designed to help keep people updated in whichever way is most convenient. We will also have a YouTube channel, which will be a supplementary service - from here, we're going to have informational videos on a wide range of topics, from policy deep-dives on complicated subjects, to Politics 101-style videos explaining the basics of politics, to videos on Alberta's history. All of these videos will also hopefully be released on services like Spotify as podcasts so that they can be used however is convenient.\xa0

How will you fund it?
Three forms - Kickstarter, merchandise, and Patreon. This Kickstarter's goal of $50,000 is the minimum necessary to run this service and keep providing accurate, unbiased information for a year. However, Kickstarter also allows us to go over our goal, and the further the APAH is funded past that goal, the more we can expand. Hitting the goal just means that we will for sure be funded, but everything past that allows us to provide an even better service. We will also be selling merchandise to raise money, and running a Patreon alongside the service to allow people to support the APAH on a monthly basis to give us a more stable income. With all three of these revenue streams, the APAH will be able to build and grow into exactly what Albertans need - a no-frills, easily accessible source of political information.

Why are you asking us for funding? Why not the government?
This one's easy - frankly, a program that's supposed to hold the government in check doesn't usually have great success when it's paid for by the government. The only way for this service to be truly capable of this is if we're by Albertans, for Albertans.\xa0
Also, crucially, the APAH will be going live before the 2019 election. That means that this site will be going up on April 7th at midnight to give Albertans more than a week to review it before going to the polls!']

story:
['Story¡Para la versión en Español, haz click aquí!




































Animation is part of our lives. It’s a magical art form, a genre of storytelling in its own right, one that excites children and adults alike. Animation involves immersing yourself in a different world, a world where the only limit is your imagination.
We are flipbook makers, but also animators, and we love imagining new things. This flipbook collection is the definitive introduction to the most important principles of animation, the rules that every animator should know. Why? Let’s find out! ;)

















Those of you familiar with our flipbooks know that they exhibit a clever trick: instead of one or two animations as in a normal flipbook, our publications feature up to six different animations (How does it work? You’ll have to figure it out by yourself ;)). And because there are 12 basic principles of animation, it’s the perfect number to create a double flip book set comprising two volumes.









Each volume features six original animations by Raúl García, one for each principle. On the first page of each sequence you’ll find an explanatory text about the principle concerned, to enable you to get a better understanding of what you see when you flip the book.
Both flipbooks come protected in their individual slipcases to prevent the pages from wearing out. These are additionally housed in a sleek double sleeve that holds them together so you can keep them in your favorite place. The collection also includes two foldable paper cubes with content relating to each principle in augmented reality format. See more about this below.

















Those of you familiar with our flipbooks know that we like a little magic! Most of our publications feature a clever trick that owes its success to a sophisticated assembly technique, and this is why we call them cinemagic flipbooks. As a result, when flipping the pages of the book, you can see up to six different animations instead of one or two as in a normal flipbook.









Our cinemagic flipbooks are surprisingly easy to use and provide an unfailing source of delight to viewers of all ages. :)

















The 12 principles are a set of core concepts based on decades of animation work carried out by Disney's "Nine Old Men”, the legendary animators largely responsible for the success of some of the most remarkable and celebrated films in the history of animated cinema, as Disney was transitioning from doing shorts to feature films in the 1930s. It was a gradual process of discovery and refinement as the animators tried to push their work to unprecedented heights.









These 12 principles were first compiled by the iconic animators Frank Thomas and Ollie Johnston in their 1981 book The Illusion of Life: Disney Animation. The 12 principles have since become known and respected as the 12 fundamental rules of animation, particularly within the American tradition (ie Disney, Warner Bros, Pixar, etc.), but they also apply to a range of animation techniques such as 3D and stop motion.

































We are absolutely thrilled to be able to develop this project in partnership with the great Raúl García, who for many years has worked for major studios such as Disney, Paramount and Hanna-Barbera on classic feature films like Who Framed Roger Rabbit, Beauty and the Beast, Aladdin, The Lion King, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, Hercules, Pocahontas and Fantasia 2000, among many others.









He also collaborated on several major productions such as Asterix Versus Caesar, The Chipmunk Adventure and The Land Before Time, and later became a sequence director for Paramount on films such as Rugrats in Paris: The Movie, The Wild Thornberrys Movie and Jimmy Neutron: Boy Genius, nominated for an Oscar for best animated feature.









In 2002 he joined Kandor Graphics as creative director, producing the award-winning short film The Tell-Tale Heart, and as a co-writer and director with Manuel Sicilia on the feature film The Missing Lynx, winner of the Goya award for best animated feature in 2008. He was director and producer of the animated feature film Extraordinary Tales, based on the tales of Edgar Allan Poe, which won him a nomination as best director of an independent feature film at the 2016 ANNIE Awards, as well as several other international awards.

            

          

In the conversations we held leading up to this project, Raúl often left us open-mouthed with the numerous insider anecdotes and stories he has accumulated over the course of his many years in the animation business. He is also remarkable for the pedagogical skills and knowledge that he shares as part of the many courses and workshops he leads around the world.









Creating the illusion of life is what the principles are all about. They help animators create characters that appear to have weight, personality and existence in a real world where the real laws of physics apply. Many animators will tell you that good animation has less to do with the design and mannerisms of your characters, and more to do with how reactive their personalities and appearance are to what's going on around them.

















The first principle is Squash and stretch. It refers to how an object changes shape in response to forces acting upon it. A bouncing ball, for example, won't always have the same shape, which will vary according to its position and consistency. Anticipation is a smaller movement that comes before a major one, and signals that the major movement is about to happen, e.g. a character bending its knees before it jumps. Staging is all about guiding the viewer's eye toward what's important within the scene, while Straight-ahead and pose-to-pose are different approaches to animating, either creating each new frame in sequence from beginning to end, or creating the key poses for each action first, then filling in the in-betweens. Follow-through and overlapping action refers to the tendency of different parts of a body to move at different speeds, while Slow-in and slow-out specifies the tendency of objects to gradually accelerate when moving from one position to another. Think about how a car will start moving slowly, before gaining momentum and speeding up.

























In the second volume you’ll learn about Arcs, a principle stemming from the observation that living things don't move in straight lines, but rather in curved trajectories. Secondary action refers to smaller movements that support the primary actions of a character. These actions make the shot clearer by emphasizing the attitude or motivation behind the movement. Then there is Timing, one of the most fundamental principles, which helps you control the speed of an action through the number of frames used to represent it. Too much realism can ruin an animation, making it appear static and boring. Instead, add some Exaggeration to your characters and objects to make them more dynamic. Solid drawing means posing characters in a way that creates a sense of volume, weight and balance; it also means being able to draw the characters from any angle or pose, with three-dimensionality in mind. And finally Appeal. This is a broad term for any qualities of a character's design that make it inherently compelling to watch. This includes the design of the character, as well as how the character is animated.

























Just like our previous Molecularis and Dots & Lines publications, The 12 Principles of Animation is a coloring flipbook as well. As can be seen in the visuals, all the sequences are line-drawn characters that are perfect for coloring, and can be redrawn and varied with an endless number of possibilities. In this way, the flipbook becomes an entertaining and fun activity not only for children, but for anyone who wants to spend some quality time alone or with their family, and get away from the screens and media for a while.









We have chosen a high quality paper suitable for all kinds of coloring techniques; use pencils, markers, watercolors, graphite, brushes, technical pens or whatever technique you prefer.\xa0

























When thinking about how to integrate the 12 principles into augmented reality, we suddenly had a brainwave: of course, cubes were needed! One cube has six sides and two cubes have 12, making them the perfect complement for the flipbook.
This feature will be available thanks to an easy-to-use iOS and Android app developed by our friends from Artivive, a revolutionary AR company based in Vienna, Austria.

















There is one cube for each volume, and they’ll be easily recognizable because of their matching colors. The cubes come in cardboard to be assembled by yourself - making them is child’s play. Once they have been assembled, simply scan the QR code included in the flip book to install the Artivive App. Open the app and see how the drawings on each side of the cube come to life while turning into real-time animations on your screen.









Most of the sequences will be shown in a loop, so you can see them in a more fluid and prolonged way. Together with the flipbook, the AR cubes will make a valuable learning tool to improve your animation skills - or you can even play dice and turn your learning process into a game :).

























If you’re familiar with our previous flipbook publications, you probably know that education plays an important role in our philosophy as a brand. We really like to push the boundaries of our editions, to look for new interactive elements that can extend the length of time users engage with the flip books and offer a unique and lasting experience.
In this new publication, education again plays a crucial role, because the flipbook is deliberately designed to help users learn about animation.The great advantage of the 12 principles being represented in a flipbook is that you can go frame by frame (or page by page, which in this case is the same), studying each principle with its respective text on the first page of each sequence. This gives you a better understanding of not only the meaning of each principle, but also how to actually apply it effectively to your animations.









Students can discover the principles in an engaging, interactive way using a medium that represents a precursor of cinema itself; at the same time, thanks to augmented reality, the collection bridges the gap between old-school and cutting-edge technology. A truly unique educational tool for all ages.









For this campaign we have come up with several appetizing bundles, which may eventually find their way onto your bookshelves. :) For those who want to get started right away with their own animations, consider picking our Animator’s Bundle with our Blanko Flipbook.
The Student’s Pack includes the flipbook and a fabulous 6-part online course by Raúl García on Drawing for Animation. In this course, Raúl explains the most important aspects of character design: surface lines, diminishing size, contact shadows, overlapping shapes, lines of action, silhouette, caricature, simple shapes, color and anatomy, and also gives some good examples of how to find inspiration to come up with interesting and convincing characters.
Raúl García’s Pack includes several books that have been published related to Raúl’s feature animation film Extraordinary Tales inspired by Edgar Allan Poe, such as our 6x1 flipbook we made some time ago featuring six original sequences from the film. After the campaign you’ll be able to choose between the art book Jack Mircala and the ART of Extraordinary Tales or the beautiful graphic novel La Caída de la Casa Usher published by La Cúpula Ediciones. Please note! The graphic novel is available only in Spanish. If you want to have both books, you can add the other one as an add-on after the campaign.









And here's the kicker: we have 10 Exclusive Original Cel Drawings from Raúl's time at Hanna-Barbera that actually made it into the series: six from The Flintstones and four from Lucky Luke. These cel drawings are hand-painted on a piece of celluloid acetate, and have been photographed over a background painting to create a frame for the finished movie. Each cel comes together with its respective background and framed, all ready to be put on display wherever you choose. Original production cels are one-of-a-kind pieces of art and a wonderful way to own and display a “moment in time” from a film, a show, or a character that you love.\xa0

































Shipping will be charged AFTER THE END OF THE CAMPAIGN, during the survey stage.
Below is an estimate of shipping costs broken down by shipping area. These are only estimates; however we commit to these prices being the maximum amount you will have to pay. The dollar symbol refers to US dollars.









Add-Ons:
All individual flipbooks and bundles can be added to your pledge AFTER THE CAMPAIGN and at the same cost. We intentionally chose not to offer Kickstarter add-ons within the campaign to keep the survey process as easy as possible for everyone. Shipping costs for add-ons will be charged by weight; this way we can calculate them as precisely as possible.









Flipboku is the brainchild of animator and designer Jossie Malis and film music composer Julie Reier. We have both been working in the world of film for many years and love all things related to animation, books and design. We loved the idea of having our own flipbook publishing house, so we started the project in 2016 and it has grown steadily since then.
Today, the Flipboku team is made up of six members, all working in our design and printing studio Boku Lab in Palma de Mallorca, Spain. The rest of the team consists of the invaluable hands of our illustrator and graphic designer Noemi Aiolo and our irreplaceable production technicians Gustavo Berdayes, Tomás Pons and José Ramón Pineda, responsible for the entire production process.









Since 2019 we have had our own printing workshop where 100% of the production is carried out. This means that the entire production process is under our control, allowing for precise results and finishes, in harmony with our commitment and obsession with design and quality. It took us several years to refine our cinemagic flip books and their optical illusion features, but thanks to the talented hands of our experienced print masters, we were able to fine-tune the concept to perfection.
Here you can get a glimpse of the super effective teamwork of the Boku crew:

























Even though we’re already experienced flipbook makers, there’s a lot of work that goes into developing a collection like The 12 Principles. For this flipbook we had the invaluable help of Raúl García, who’s already devoted many hours of work in creating the 12 animated sequences of the flipbook. These 12 sequences had to be adapted to the flipbook format; we had to make several prototypes until we got the right order, layout, paper and design. Finally we needed to think about how to include the two paper cubes that come with the collection.
Now we need your help to complete the final step – to bring The 12 Principles to life and secure a minimum print run of 1,000 units. While our print team works on the production, we'll focus on the task of integrating the 12 animations into augmented reality format, so that they’re ready when the flipbooks are shipped.



































Special thanks to Raúl García, Noemi Aiolo, Artivive, Emilio Bernárdez, \xa0Matías Arévalo, Hartley Moorhouse, Natasha Blass, Marmoset Music,\xa0Clancy Magnuson, Podington Bear, IEB Institut d'Estudis Balearics, Beatriz Tejeiro y Jonathan García.']
