story:
['StorySilver Sable (Silver Sablinova) is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. She is usually depicted as a mercenary, hunter of war criminals, leader of the Wild Pack, and owner of Silver Sable International. While not a criminal, her work as a mercenary has sometimes brought her into conflict with several superheroes. Silver Sable is primarily an ally and sometimes enemy of Spider-Man.
The character has appeared in several media adaptations over the years, including animated series and video games.
In this film, Silver Sable has to rescue her younger sister Laybird from a group of ex-military solders known as the Blue Shrikes.

So a little backstory about Ladybird and the Blue Shrikes:
Ladybird is the younger sister of Silver Sable who is the sole protector of Symkaria (A former soldier in the Symkarian Army) and also the CEO of Sable International. Ladybird is looks up to Silver Sable and wants to follow in her footsteps. Ladybird is less serious and less organized than Silver Sable where she does things on the fly, very outspoken. She’s in her mid 20s so she’s on the verge of creating her own identity.
Blue Shrikes are an ex-militant group from Estonia 🇪🇪 who are against the partnership of Estonia and Symkaria (Symkaria is a fictitious country in the Marvel Universe which is based on the country of Latvia 🇱🇻)
The Blue Shrike soldiers are working for the tyrant Andris who was second in command of the Blue Shrikes to the father of Silver Sable and Ladybird but the father fell in love with a Symkarian woman so he left Estonia 🇪🇪 and his position as the leader of the Blue Shrikes thus creating a personal war between Silver Sable and the Blue Shrikes. The Blue Shrikes consist of soldiers that the country of Estonia 🇪🇪 forgot after the Symkaria-Estonia wars and they never mentally healed after those wars before the two respected countries decided to sign a treaty that ensured one would help each other out if they ever encountered financial struggles.']

blurb: Produce an animated video based on one of Matt Limo's "Zines" that he produced from 1992 to 1997.
name: Matt Limo's "Zine" Brought to Life
story:
['Story


One of the drawings by academy award nominated cartoonist Bill Plympton that will be used in the film. Here, Matt and Benny are making their selection of beers to swipe from the Flying J.





This video project lifts one of the hilarious stories by Matt Limo and his friend Benny stealing beer from a convenience store in Eureka, California in Da (Drunken) Tortise & Da (Vigalante) Hare. The story is from one of Matt's accounts published in the Limo Zine anthology by FLUKE PUBLISHING. This escapade is to brought to life with animated characters drawn by academy award nominated cartoonist Bill Plympton with voice over by his lifelong friend Bennie Goodson.
Matthew Markus, aka Matt Limo, was born in Little Rock, Arkansas in 1975. In his youth he was known as an iconoclast who shunned traditional societal norms. He traveled across the USA as a virtual vagabond seeking, and finding, unusual and often bizarre adventures with his close friends. While traveling, he would constantly write about his adventures in a notebook that he eventually published between 1992 to 1997 in three "Limo Zines" as his homemade magazine. He was a brilliant storyteller. A compilation of his stories was collected after his premature death in 2021 and published by FLUKE PIUBLISHING as The Limo Zine Anthology. \xa0
You can order a copy of Matt's "Zines" here:\xa0 https://fluke.bigcartel.com/product/limo-zine-anthology\xa0
Bill Plympton's academy nominated work can be found here: https://www.plymptoons.com/
Filmmaker Ned Thanhouser's work may be seen here: https://vimeo.com/thanhouser
Bennie Goodson runs Langlitz Leathers based in Portland, Oregon, you can see their products here: https://www.langlitz.com/






Poster that announces Matt's animated film from his Limo Zine.








Face plate image for the DVD reward']

blurb: An original graphic novel about growing up, fitting in, and a witch from a bottle determined to wreak havoc!
name: Isabella & Blodwen
story:
["StoryIsabella and Blodwen is the latest book from Rachael Smith, creator of Wired Up Wrong, Stand in your Power, and the critically-acclaimed record of the Covid Pandemic, Quarantine Comix.

Isabella & Blodwen is a 200 page full colour hardback with a trim size of 240mm x 170mm portrait (that's 9.5 in x 6.6in if you'd prefer imperial!)




Isabella & Blodwen by Rachael Smith













The story follows sixteen year-old Isabella who has been granted early admission to the prestigious University of Oxford. Academically gifted, but lacking in social skills, she finds navigating the hallowed halls a trial she can’t study her way out of. Mixing with older students, and struggling to find her place, she sets her heart on the coveted summer internship with her hero, Professor MacLeod. While wondering how to get the letter of recommendation she needs to be considered, she accidentally drops an exhibit from a museum she’s visiting in her bag... and Blodwen, the Witch from the Bottle enters her life!




Introductions





After centuries trapped in a little silver flask, Blodwen is thrilled to find herself in the thick of things in a University dorm, and is determined to make the most of her newfound freedom. Isabella makes a number of frantic attempts to return the bottle, and Blodwen, to the museum and rid herself of this meddling witch, all foiled. After a night out goes terribly wrong, Blodwen and Isabella argue, prompting Blodwen to cast a terrible curse on Isabella... and life gets even more difficult!




Realisations...





Aimed at a young adult audience, and exploring themes of friendship, growing up, and finding your place in the world, Isabella and Blodwen is a story that will resonate with anyone who has ever felt alone and that the world is against them.










Of course!

































Rachael Smith is a comic artist and writer based in the UK. She has created numerous, critically acclaimed comic books including House Party, Artificial Flowers, Wired Up Wrong, and Quaratine Comix. Rachael has also \xa0worked on Titan's Doctor Who Comic series, and is a regular contributor to Empathize This, a website which gives a platform to marginalised voices through the medium of comics.
Isabella & Blodwen is the latest title from Cast Iron Books, a boutique independent publisher of graphic novels and illustrated books\xa0based in the UK. It was founded in the summer of 2020 by Lizzie Kaye, formerly of SelfMadeHero, Titan Comics and Unbound.
The Cast Iron Books ethos is founded on empowering authors and artists to create stories that stay with a reader long after the last page has been turned.




















A5 Bookplate and A4 Art Print






We want to keep things simple for you – the book is the main reward!
Every backer will also receive the Ebook edition and you can also \xa0receive a bookmark, bookplate, art print... or commission a pet portrait from Rachael!\xa0
See below for some examples of the rewards on offer...

































We want to give as many people as possible the opportunity to get on \xa0board with this project, in whatever way suits you, so please get \xa0in\xa0touch if you'd like to discuss combining reward levels!"]

blurb: Deluxe hardback editions of Vincenzo Ferriero and Ray Chou's dieselpunk airship adventure comic, in its entirety for the first time.
name: Skies of Fire: Collected Edition
profile: {"id":4377247,"project_id":4377247,"state":"active","state_changed_at":1666295708,"name":"Skies of Fire: Collected Edition","blurb":"Deluxe hardback editions of Vincenzo Ferriero and Ray Chou's dieselpunk airship adventure comic, in its entirety for the first time.","background_color":"","text_color":"","link_background_color":"","link_text_color":"","link_text":"Preorder Here","link_url":"https://skies-of-fire-collected-edition.backerkit.com/hosted_preordershttp://www.myth.works","show_feature_image":false,"background_image_opacity":0.8,"should_show_feature_image_section":true,"feature_image_attributes":{"image_urls":{"default":"https://i.kickstarter.com/assets/037/960/368/88ef9baf21f8a907ebb69d17dee29047_original.jpg?anim=false&fit=cover&gravity=auto&height=873&origin=ugc&q=92&width=1552&sig=6hsVHvndZ2afX1XXT3WlHKL94Z0aZXTNQKGfmCbKifw%3D","baseball_card":"https://i.kickstarter.com/assets/037/960/368/88ef9baf21f8a907ebb69d17dee29047_original.jpg?anim=false&fit=cover&gravity=auto&height=315&origin=ugc&q=92&width=560&sig=Or4ZefbvSc9CqQHAOe9QxxTSHLmh%2FNGn85eJT5J1h%2Bw%3D"}}}
story:
["Story









Skies of Fire is a limited comic \xa0series by Vincenzo Ferriero and Ray Chou, with art by Pablo Peppino and \xa0Bryan Valenza. Skies was launched in 2014 and has remained 100% \xa0independent through crowdfunding and the support of our fans.









This campaign's goal is to raise funds to print the collected editions of Skies of Fire, comprising of two hardcover books encompassing the original eight issue run and a hardcover slipcase to fit both editions.\xa0









Skies of Fire takes place in the Aquilan Empire, a kingdom where \xa0airship travel has become the dominant means of transportation, \xa0commerce, and war. In the center of the Empire lies a monstrous, \xa0never-ending storm called The Expanse.










In Issue One, the raider Delmonte \xa0orchestrates a surprise attack on the key trade outpost, Port Prince. \xa0His actions prompt Royal Guard Captain Helen Pierce to volunteer for an \xa0expedition to bring him to justice.










In Issue Two, Captain Pierce enlists the help of the elusive William.









Issue Three follows the pair as they recruit members for their mission in the border town of Copperhead.









In Issue Four, the crew of the Zephyr comes together despite their differences.









Issue Five follows the Zephyr as they embark into the Expanse.









Issue Six finds the Zephyr in enemy territory deep in the heart of the storm.









In Issue Seven, the Zephyr attempts to complete the mission.









In Issue Eight, the crew of the Zephyr reconciles with fate.






















The front side of the Standard Edition Slipcase. 








































The backside of the standard edition slipcase. 















\xa0The Kickstarter exclusive Collector's Edition features full clothbound covers of the Zephyr and Callisto in gold emboss:\xa0









\xa0These beautiful covers were rendered by resident ship designer Alex Bucur, who created full 3D models of each ship in order to compile the covers.\xa0









The Collector's Edition will also feature a different slipcase cover featuring an art deco pattern designed by series cartographer Joseph Vandal.\xa0









\xa0This Collector's Edition will be printed in extremely limited quantities based off of amount ordered on this Kickstarter and will never be reprinted.\xa0









\xa0All of our hardcover books will feature the highest quality specifications and manufacturing as our previous projects.\xa0









The interiors of book editions will be the same with the primary differences between editions are in covers and slipcases.\xa0




















The budget for this Kickstarter accounts for the printing and shipping of items from this campaign.

















Like the rest of the world, we've been impacted by recent global events that have made global trade and commerce more difficult and expensive. If you \xa0visit our past campaigns, you can track our monitoring of the situation as it has unfolded over the past two years.

To mitigate the risk, we are charging for shipping separately closer to the campaign fulfillment. Fulfillment will be handled by our warehousing partners in the United States and Europe. We've learn a lot over the past year on how to work with warehouses, and we're working to implement improvements on the process across the board, which we've detailed in the Skies of Fire #8 Post-Mortem here. \xa0


















The creative minds behind Skies of Fire and Mythopoeia, Vincenzo Ferriero \xa0and Ray Chou have been collaborating on creative projects since 2008 despite living 5,437 miles apart. \xa0Find us on Instagram and Tik Tok: @mythopoeians.









Pablo Peppino is a an illustrator from Argentina with a focus on sequential art. @pablopop_

Bryan Valenza is a prolific artist based in \xa0Jakarta, Indonesia. He currently occupies his time coloring various \xa0projects from top publishers in the industry. @bryan_valenza









Alexandur Bucur is an architect and \xa0illustrator with an interest in history and military hardware of all \xa0kinds. When not at his drawing table he can be found standing at \xa0attention in a swanky uniform for the benefit of the Military Traditions \xa0branch of the Romanian Army. @wingsofwrath

Cristian Docolomansky Cerda (C.D.C.) is a \xa0Barcelona-born inker and letterer based in Chile. He's worked with \xa0several publishers such as Alterna Comics, IDW, and Ariete Producciones. \xa0You can find him here.










This campaign represents the culmination of eight years of sweat, pain, and tears. When we launched Skies of Fire in 2014, all we had was a dream, a script, and a few pages of artwork.\xa0

Though we were confident we'd be able to tell our story, we never could imagine the journey Skies of Fire has taken us. \xa0From Bucharest to San Diego, we've exhibited at comic conventions all over the world, \xa0learning about the business of creativity along the way, which at times has been both rewarding and excruciating.\xa0

Still, this project - and every one that has come since - represents the manifestation of our dreams and aspirations as young filmmakers, all those years ago.\xa0

\xa0If you're a supporter of Skies of Fire, past or present, thank you from the bottom of our hearts.\xa0

We couldn't have done it without you.\xa0

- Ray and Vince"]

blurb: Why hasn't anyone made tape from football glove material before?
name: Football-Glove Tape
story: ['StoryMeet Football-Glove Tape.I always hated the extra material and poor performance in wet conditions that a standard football glove gave to its user. The only attribute about a glove I liked was the grippy material. I simply have taken this grippy material and made it into a roll of tape that can be cut to a users liking.']

blurb: A fourth axis to my CNC machine for my business to keep up with the demand of wooden items that we create for our business.
name: Custom built CNC machine for Kenny's Custom Woodworking
story: ['StoryThree years ago I was in between jobs and decided that I needed to be creative to find work in the field of carpentry. I wanted to purchase a CNC machine to start a cabinet shop. After being turned town by numerous banks for a small business start up loan, my wife and I decided to finance it ourselves. We drained our savings and tapped out our credit cards. The end result was a machine that not only worked, but launched our business to new levels. Only a year and a half after completion I am now working full time making monograms and wood letters. I now have two employees and we sell to 55 stores around the US! Building my own CNC machine has been life changing for me! Now comes the problem, we want to add another axis to one of our machines. Our business is booming, in our first year from August to December we had over $60,000 in sales. Pretty impressive for just starting. In our second year we are on track to double that. Any bank would lend us money to expand- WRONG! Even though our credit is excellent, we are being denied business loans because we tapped out our credit cards. Are we getting them paid down, sure, but slowly with as high as the interests rates are. This project will allow us to expand our business further, by creating another dimension so we can keep up with the demand of our stores. We are grateful that websites like this exist, so that small business can flourish even with lack of generosity from the banking industry.']

blurb: The Pixelduino is a tiny Arduino-compatible microcontroller with a full color 1.5" OLED display + MicroSD built-in!
name: Pixelduino - The Arduino with an awesome OLED display!
story:
['StoryThe Pixelduino is an Arduino-compatible microcontroller that features a 1.5" 128x128 pixel color OLED screen and a MicroSD slot! There are all sorts of things you can do with a device like this. You can create wearables like a watch, bracelet, pendant, or buckle that displays color images, attach sensors and display data in text or visual form, display debug information, create a graphics user interface, or even make simple retro games.







Features / specifications
Processor : Atmel Atmega328P @ 5V / 16MHz
IO pins : 14 digital, 6 analog 
Memory : 32K flash, 2K RAM
Voltage regulator : TPS61202 5V boost converter
Input voltage : 1.5 - 5.5V recommended
Supply current : 100mA @ 0.5V, 1A @ 3V, 1.3A @ 3.7V
Power connector : JST PH (standard for small LiPo cells)\xa0 
Display : 128x128 16-bit color 1.5" (38mm) OLED w/ SSD1351 driver
PCB Size : 1.7" x 1.7" (43 x 43mm)








The display on the Pixelduino is compatible with Adafruit's GFX library. This 
library provides functions for blitting images, drawing primitives like 
lines and circles, and even includes basic bitmapped font support. The theoretical maximum speed of this display when streaming from the SD card and refreshing the entire screen is ~10 
fps. This is based on the speed of the SPI bus and the amount of 
data that needs to be pushed around.The display controller also has 
some graphics acceleration built in, allowing you to redraw only specific parts of the screen (enabling sprite rendering by tracking dirty rectangles) or change the display offset to scroll vertically. (Of course, if you want to do horizontal scrolling in hardware, you can always rotate the screen by 90 degrees!)







The Pixelduino is also compatible with the Arduino's SPI and SD libraries. Communication with the display and MicroSD card are both handled with 
the SPI bus on pins 10-13.\xa0 Pins 8 and 9 are also used to command the 
display.\xa0 Aside from these, the rest of the pins are available for any 
use.\xa0 The I2C bus for example is available on pins A4 and A5. 









In the image above you can see the board includes a convenient 2mm JST PH connector, just like those found on small LiPo batteries and some alkaline battery packs.The board can run on 1 to 3 alkaline, lithium, or NiMh batteries, as well as single-cell LiPo batteries. The on-board boost regulator efficiently steps the voltage up to the 5V the board requires, and has a built in linear regulator to step the voltage down when needed.







New firmware can be loaded using the Arduino IDE with the same USB serial FTDI programmers boards like the Arduino Pro use, or with an ISP programmer using a pogo-pin adapter.The circuit seen in the video is a proof of concept using the same screen and processor that will be used on the final board. The final design is complete and ready to go into production as soon as we reach our funding goal.







The Pixelduino is open hardware and the schematics and PCB layout 
will be made available so you can manufacture them yourself or learn
 from the design and improve upon it!

Production timelineHere is the timeline for completing each phase of the project:
Design schematic - DONE

Layout PCB - DONE

Create Bill of Materials - DONE

Assemble and test prototype - DONE

Acquire funding on Kickstarter - IN PROGRESS

Thank everyone for their support!
Order parts + get first round of PCBs made for testing
Assemble and test boards
If necessary, correct any mistakes and order another round of PCBs for testing
Order final assembled boards
Burn bootloader onto all boards
Ship!
Why Kickstarter?We set out to design this board after seeing a similar product with a 
tiny monochrome screen that we thought we could improve upon. But hardware is expensive, and color OLED screens even more so. To produce these boards at this price point, we need to order several hundred of them at a time. And we don't even know if there's a market for it. But we hope there is!Please back our Kickstarter.\xa0 Thank you! - Rabid PrototypesPS:The chiptunes in our pitch video were graciously provided under a Creative Commons license by 'RoccoW'.\xa0 If you enjoyed them you can find more of his stuff on Youtube and Soundcloud.']

blurb: Makeosity's young makers engineered a high tech energy scooter with portable generator to charge iphones and other electronic devices.
name: Makeosity Energy Scooter
story:
["Story


Newest Prototype Modeled with Fusion 360






Presenting at the Education Keynote at Autodesk University





The energy scooter with its portable crank generator charges electronic devices when it's foot-peddled by its riders. \xa0The portable generator with AC adapter (patent pending) can be detached and attached to any scooter, bike or longboard. It was designed and built by Makeosity with young makers, ages 11-13, who wanted to create a product to encourage more urban youth, like themselves, to get out and exercise more. Their answer is to promote riding scooters, bikes and longboards through being digitally connected and fully charged through exercise. \xa0We have built two prototypes of the energy scooter and its portable charging device, with the energy scooters' young makers, and are raising funds to design, build and test a final model (scooter and portable energy generator). We will produce limited editions that we will test drive with youth in New York City. \xa0Through their feedback, we will tweak our final designs and create the final product(s), (scooter and energy generator and/or portable generator) and specifications for manufacturing."]

blurb:
Backup and charging are daily tasks for most smartphone users. 
Is there a better and smarter way to do it ? Syncube does.
name: Syncube -  Your Smart Phone's New Best Friend
story:
['Story















Using different cloud services gives you more storage space. It's awesome, but always forgetting which cloud you stored the file is cumbersome. The Syncube App simply integrates all clouds together as one big cloud. 







Not only does Syncube allow you to store files into your USB hard disk at home, but it also enables you to retrieve those files wherever you go. You never have to worry about limited storage space for your smartphone.





















You'll need an HTML5 capable browser to see this content.





Play


































Replay with sound









Play with  sound












00:00


00:00


















































Want to take down the photos once shared, but cannot find it or do not remember with whom you shared it with? Syncube's advance sharing control features allows you to determine how long a file will be shared, to who, and how many times the item can be accessed, etc. You will have full control at all time.















Once you store your media files on Syncube, you can stream the movie to your smartphone directly without using any additional space on your phone. Use your smartphone to watch movies will never be a problem.





















You'll need an HTML5 capable browser to see this content.





Play


































Replay with sound









Play with  sound












00:00


00:00


































Just put your smartphone on Syncube, your smartphone will be charged wirelessly without plug in any cable.Press Coverage







A device that automatically and securely backs-up media files while simultaneously charging smartphones wirelessly has been launched on Kickstarter.\xa0















Backup and charging are the daily work for most of smartphone users. 
Is there a better and smarter way to do it ? Syncube does.














\xa0De\xa0Syncube\xa0op Kickstarter wil het makkelijker maken om je iPhone-bestanden te synchroniseren. Door je iPhone op dit apparaat te leggen, kun je namelijk alle bestanden op je iPhone hier naartoe verplaatsen. Tegelijkertijd wordt hij draadloos opgeladen.



















As we interact with our smartphone in new different ways, we store pictures, videos, and files every day but very quickly we begin to run out of memory, yet we are too lazy to deal with it. According to our research, the majority of smartphone users backup and clean up their device every 1-2 months or they do it when they are forced to.

Backing up and cleaning up our smartphones shouldn't be hard ! We have too many things in life that needs cleaning, our desks, living rooms, kitchens, and bathrooms. Our smartphones shouldn't take time to clean up!















Dropbox, Google Drive, Box... All of them are free and easy to use, but I have a "pictures" folder in every cloud ! How do I keep track of these pictures? If I have to delete it which public clouds do I need to go to? Can they backup each other? Do I actually have a backup saved in my home?
\xa0















As the demand for PC continues to drop, more and more people now use smartphone and tablets instead of computers. However, as technology nowadays evolve in a tremendous speed, most functions of smartphone and tablets may become too complicated for some of the users who never use computers in the past.







For those who are fluent with computers, the process of backing up files are complicated. We are stuck with the small memory size mobile device we had. Cloud services like Google Drive and Dropbox provide automatic backup services for free, but those free cloud space are never enough. Additional cloud storage space meant additional costs for the user.

 








\xa0Although Google+ has a powerful fix photo function but it is extremely difficult to post those fixed photos onto Facebook. This is because large public cloud companies will not collaborate with each other.





















You'll need an HTML5 capable browser to see this content.





Play


































Replay with sound









Play with  sound












00:00


00:00


































































You need to have :
A network router which can be connected to Syncube through cable or WiFi.
A portable USB hard drive which is not provided in the pledge program. The USB hard drive must be put inside the Syncube, the usb cable inside will connect the drive to the Syncube.

Attach a wireless charging card to the back of your smartphone and connect it to the micro USB or Lightening port; alternatively you can use phone cases which are built-in with wireless charging function.



















Wireless ChargingIn order to charge your phone wirelessly, your need to attach a wireless charging card to your smartphone first. Then, put your smartphone on top of Syncube, your smartphone will be charged through the wireless charging card.For the following functions, Syncube needs to connect to you WIFI router at home with a ethernet cable or via WIFI. Your smartphone needs to connect to Syncube through the internet when you are outside or through the local network when connect to your router at home.File BackupWhen you put your smartphone on top of Syncube, your smartphone will receive a push message that asks if you want to backup your files. Press "yes" then the app will backup new files while files that had been backed up will be bypassed.Remote File AccessYou can use the Syncube App to access all files in the Hard Drive.Cloud ManagementFollow the Syncube App's set-up process and authorize Syncube App's link with your public clouds. Then, all the files in your public clouds such as Google Drive, Dropbox can be accessed and managed in the Syncube App.']

blurb: A Fine Art photography book for young children that fosters connection, creativity, and communication.
name: TODDLERHOOD: Reality Abstracted
story:
['StoryFine Art, but Make it For LittlesHello, world! I'm Jessica Marie Francis and this is my first book.





How We Got HereI chose Kickstarter for this project because it gives me the chance to be thoughtful about how this book reaches its audience.\xa0My path to publishing a children’s book is anything but conventional.\xa0 By trade, I’m a children and family photographer.\xa0 I have a BA in Philosophy and an MAMC in web design and online communication, both from the University of Florida (inserting the requisite #GoGators here). \xa0I started my career at UF as an architecture student, and my favorite job title I’ve ever earned is “bread shaper” at a local French-inspired bakery.\xa0With that background in mind, this part sounds a little less off the wall: I want to create and publish Fine Art books for toddlers that foster creativity, connection, and communication.\xa0 So much of my experience, so much of myself is wrapped up in this project.What makes this book special?\xa0 It’s designed to start conversations.\xa0 We love open-ended play and imaginative exploration; this book brings that to you.\xa0 “What is that thing?”, “I’ve never looked at a prepackaged snack quite that way before…” \xa0All the images in the book are Fine Art quality images taken in the thick of raising a toddler with a Pixel 8 Pro – the tool I almost always have on hand as a busy mom.\xa0 I want to show people the beauty of the smallest moments.\xa0 The light. The shadow. The shape of childhood.I so appreciate this platform and the chance to share my work with a larger audience.\xa0 Thank you for stopping by!\xa0 Please share as you see fit.<3 JMF\xa0





The BookThis will be a 6" x 6" board book with a soft-touch matte cover. \xa0Perfect for little fingers. \xa0Designed to create a tactile experience, this visually stimulating book focuses nearly as much on how it feels to interact with the cover and pages as the importance of the images and words contained on them. \xa0Because of the board book format, the smallest first run available to us was 500 copies... hence the Kickstarter campaign.']

blurb: An upper young adult adventure with pirates, cursed princesses, carnivals/circus troupes, and a strong female main character.
name: The Wayward Sword | An Upper YA Fantasy Adventure
story:
["Story

FROM THE AUTHOR




I wanted a place where I could publish MY story; a place where it would be supported and not be asked to fit into whatever box is the biggest trend at the moment. I remember worrying I wouldn’t be able to find a place I wanted to call “home” for my story—that no place would quite fit all the details I’d imagined. But Story-weaver wanted to work\xa0with\xa0me and my story instead of just trying to make a buck, and while I did have to spend quite a while ruminating on my decision, I’m glad I decided to come to a publisher that had my best interest at heart.

FROM THE PUBLISHER




Our mission at Story-weaver Publishing is to provide a home for authors who write gritty but God-honoring fiction. It is a privilege to bring stories like Lindsay’s into the world, and we’re so excited to sign her on as a Storyweaver author!The world of Valara is one filled with mystery, curses, deities, legends, and more. From dreaded pirates to Carnivale, princesses and monsters, there is something for readers to dive into and enjoy. We cannot wait for you to join Lindsay in publishing her debut novel!

ABOUT THE BOOK




As long as Aaren poses as a man, none of her crewmates aboard the Crimson Lord can guess at her mysterious past. But when her disguise is exposed, she must return to land to prove herself and regain her crew’s trust. Her mission is simple: steal a ring off the king’s neck.But a brutal murderer lurks on the coast, one who seems bent on exposing her whereabouts. Pressured by her exile, chased by a serial killer, Aaren races to earn her spot back at sea before she loses her head—or herself.

MEET THE AUTHOR










Lindsay Raymon-James decided in third grade that she was supposed to be an author; it just took a few years for her stories to catch up. A long time lover of fantasy, it’s no surprise she ended up crafting her own worlds to gallivant off to when she was supposed to be working on “taxes”. Now, she can’t imagine life without stories as she continues to challenge herself to step into new and fantastical projects, pushing herself to always be growing in her craft. \xa0She does find referring to herself in the third-person a bit strange, though.

REWARD OPTIONS
































































Stretch Goals





Stretch Goal #1: HARDCOVER EDITIONThere's something beautiful about a hardcover book, which is why if we hit $4,500 during the campaign, we'll be able to publish a hardcover edition of The Wayward Sword.





Stretch Goal #2: CHARACTER ARTNothing brings a story to life like artwork from your world. Getting to see the things that have lived rent-free in your mind for years (sometimes decades) is an amazing feeling!If we can raise $5,000, that will allow us to find the right artist to match the style and feel of Lindsay's world and bring her characters to life in a whole new way.

BONUS MATERIALS




As a bonus to all our backers, we offer additional “perks” for supporting our authors as a way of thanking you.

All ebooks are DRM-free, which means you can load them on any device: Kindle, Nook, Kobo e-reader, computer, smartphone, or tablet without any locking mechanisms that prevent you from moving files from place to place.

Your name will be printed in the acknowledgment section so everyone will see that you are an awesome supporter of the project (you can opt-out if you choose or specify the name of a loved one instead).

All rewards include an invitation to the virtual launch party (date TBD closer to publication) where you’ll get to hang out with the author and ask questions about the book.

Join the Author Community and receive special updates from the author specifically over the publishing process.


ABOUT THE PROJECT




We’re up-front about what the costs are with our authors, and we also want to be transparent with the backers too. Everything the campaign covers is listed out below in full. When you back a project, you’re helping the author get the professional editing, cover design, and layout a book deserves.

Cover Design: covers ebook/paperback design.

Editing: This book will go through professional editing and proofreading.

Layout Design: Formatting the book will bring the polish that readers expect.

Kickstarter fees: 10% comes off the top of each campaign.

Publishing Fees: Our publishing fee covers things like website maintenance and subscriptions used to run the publisher.

Printing: Cost of printing the books.


ABOUT SHIPPING




Shipping is not included in the prices. This is because single books are far less expensive to ship than others that will require a bigger box or envelope. Prices are based on USPS Ground Advantage shipping rates and ensure your rewards arrive in a timely manner once published.We are currently limiting shipping to within the United States due to international shipping costs.

TIMELINE




Production of a quality book is no mean feat. There are several rounds of editing, revisions on the cover designs, formatting, layout, and proofreading. Most take a month or more to complete as we work with our authors to bring their vision to life. Here’s a general guideline you can expect:

Months 1-3: Developmental edits, cover design concepts, revisions

Months 4-6: Finalizing cover design, Line edits or copyedits depending on which is needed

Months 7-9: Finalizing edits, proofread, layout and formatting

Months 10-12: Prepping files, printing and shipping books, full publishing launch


WHY KICKSTARTER?




Story-weaver Publishing uses Kickstarter as a way to eliminate or minimize author fees while making sure our editors, designers, and formatters get paid based on their rates. It also allows us to work with our authors on extras like character art or map design, which can be included in the campaign if they choose to have it.\xa0The other awesome aspect of Kickstarter is that you get to support an author before their book is published! You are the foundation of their reader base. You get to help them achieve their dreams of writing and publishing books while getting rewards regular buyers won’t get after this.

NEW TO KICKSTARTER?




If you're new to pledging on Kickstarter, here's a short overview of how it works.Kickstarter is a platform that allows artists and creatives to crowdfund projects directly. If the campaign goal is reached within the allotted time, then your card will be charged and we will begin working to fulfill those orders by the dates stated on the reward. If the goal is not reached, your card will NOT be charged.\xa0After the campaign is complete, we'll reach out for additional info like shipping addresses, so please make sure you are watching for things like that after the campaign.

CREATIVE TEAM




When he published his first book in 2020, he saw the need for a publisher focused on Christian Fiction dealing with harder topics. After much prayer, he started Story-weaver Publishing, not only for his books, but to build a home for like-minded authors seeking to honor God through the art of storytelling.





From playing make-believe with her backyard neighbors to now working on her own science fantasy trilogy, Emily Vest has always loved everything storytelling. She is thrilled to join the team at Story-weaver Publishing, and she aims to hone her passion for writing and editing by helping fellow writers polish their own stories and reach publishing success!While in school, Emily worked as The Cedarville Review editor-in-chief, a workshop leader, and a writing center tutor before getting her start as a freelance editor with Honeycomb Author Services. Currently, she is working on her debut novel and her trilogy but also has published poetry and short-form prose in The Albion Review, Adelaide Literary Magazine, and The Cedarville Review. She has a Bachelor's degree in English Literature with three minors in Creative Writing, Editing & Publishing, and Biblical Studies from Cedarville University.Brianna currently works as an associate editor and project coordinator for Innovo Publishing LLC. She is also a freelance editor for the Christian Publishing Portal. Now, she's excited to join the team at Story-weaver Publishing! She has a Bachelor's in Professional Writing and Information Design, a minor in Editing and Publishing, and a minor in Biblical Studies from Cedarville University.Cheyenne van Langevelde has loved storytelling since she was little, making up tragic adventures with Playmobil and turning every playground into a sinking ship. Being a voracious reader as long as she can remember, she began writing her own stories back in 2014. Since then, she has successfully self-published two novels and has experience in both the traditional and indie publishing spheres.\xa0Benita Thompson has been writing since she was a five-year-old inspired by the Bobbsey Twins and Little House on the Prairie. During high school she self-published three books, discovering a love for book design in the process. She has been offering cover design and formatting services since 2016, with a commitment to providing professional-tier design on an indie author budget. Her specialty focus is in fantasy and speculative fiction

ABOUT THE PUBLISHER




At Story-weaver Publishing LLC, our aim is to honor God and the beautiful art of storytelling. One way we do this is by publishing intriguing, meaningful, and intricately woven narratives, and not shying away from the darker side of life.That's why we provide a home for authors tackling difficult topics and challenging questions, all while staying true to God's word. The Bible doesn't shirk from things, and we don't believe authors should either.The Christian publishing industry has focused on two primary areas: Romance and Non-Fiction. Between those, there are amazing indie publishers providing a space for Christian Fiction. However, S. D. Howard, the founder of Story-weaver Publishing, noticed there were few places for books of a darker tone or that dealt with more sensitive topics.The long-term goal is to provide a home for Christian authors who feel called to tackle the darkness to thereby shine the Light. This by no means excludes authors who write lighter material or ones that are not overtly Christian in nature.\xa0S. D. Howard's publishing journey started with hybrid publishing, and he saw the tremendous opportunity it provided to authors who wanted to go indie, but didn't necessarily have all the resources.The combination of crowdfunding and hybrid publishing brings together so many possibilities, which is why we aim to pair the two together for the benefit of the author.​By crowdfunding the cost of publishing, the author is not only able to cover their costs to publish, but also pre-sell their book to family, friends, and fans. Doing this also allows authors to have stretch goals like getting a hardcover edition, or paying a narrator to create an audiobook."]

blurb: Awareness gifts for every affliction and all cancer colors, not just pink
name: Awareness gifts for all. All colors represented.
story:
['Story


Come see the rest in person!






Small bite of awareness



I am a breast cancer survivor. My husband got diagnosed with kidney cancer soon after that. I could find pink ribbons everywhere, but no other color. I make gifts for cancer patients along with every other awareness color out there to represent ALL people who need support. There are many gifts I can't make in 32 different colors, so I make up in one-of-a-kind gifts. I am trying to keep my price point down to where most people could afford my product. I am also making jewelry for my customers and have decided to involve people to the extent that I am going to have a "make your own jewelry" table. I volunteer at Christmas Unlimited and have always catered to children, so I have many unique pieces that they could not buy (or make) anywhere else. My least expensive item will be $1.00 and my most expensive will be $60.00. The $60.00 items are blankets that I hand make. Anyone can order anything I make in another color or more customized to them. I want my space at the flea market to look more like a store than a booth. I am needing shelving and display money, along with some unfinished projects I still have to add. Next are t-shirts, planters, terrariums and rosaries.']

blurb: I make handcrafted chainmaille jewelry.  Celtic stars are one of my favorite things to make.  There are so many color combinations!
name: Chained Creativity Celtic Stars
story:
["StoryAbout this projectHello, my name is Michelle Poirier, and I like spending all my time weaving metal. Chainmaille jewelry is my passion.I have some crazy wonderful ideas for new things to make, but they will require a lot more supplies to make. This is where you come in!If you support my Kickstarter campaign by buying any of the reward tiers listed here you'll help fund my fall line of jewelry, and also get yourself some great jewelry! (or get some great jewelry for your family, or friends, or even all of you!).


Tons of colors!



These pieces are very lightweight :) They are made using anodized (colored) aluminum and the color will not tarnish or fade.There are lots of colors to choose from (you can mix colors together, or just choose one color, it's up to you!) Matte colors: silver, black, red, orange, yellow, gold, bronze, green, blue, purple, violet, pinkshiny colors (as seen below): silver, black, red, orange, yellow, gold, champagne, black ice, bronze, green, seafoam green, blue, sky blue, purple, lavender, rose.


Lots of color choices



\xa0A look at the earrings:  They are 1 inch long, not counting the earring hooks.  Hooks are plated iron and nickle free.  Don't worry, these earrings are very light weight!


Celtic star earrings



\xa0The Celtic stars on the necklaces are 1.5 inches wide.\xa0 You get to choose the length of your necklace, between 16 to 24 inches long :)


Celtic star necklace



\xa0The bracelets are the european 4 in 1 weave and you will be able to choose what color(s) and length you would like them to be (up to 8 inches long max).


Bracelets






Bracelets



Project Goal:$700 for supplies to make new jewelry
$300 to pay cost of advertising (if no one knows they exist, they won't sell!)I love weaving metal, and with your help I can make new designs!If I meet my goal I will be ecstatic and love you all <3If by chance I happen to surpass my goal I will spend the money on:-more chainmaille supplies -pendants, charms and beads (trust me when I say they add up fast!)

-photoshootStretch goals:If we surpass my goal, I will add new reward tiers :) (if you want one of these, you will have to purchase them on top of your initial pledge).-If we reach $1000 Locked.-If we reach$1500 Locked.-If we reach $2000 Locked.If we go over that amount, I will add more reward tiers :)Here is a picture of me at the last show I did: 


Convention time :)"]

blurb: A series of unique crystal jewelry pieces inspired by nature and God.  Reminders of natural beauty and where we come from.
name: Natural Relics - Handcrafted Crystal Jewelry
story:
["StoryWelcome and thank you for visiting my project page!  My goal is to expand my online shop with a large variety of handmade products created from crystals, minerals, clay, metals, and other natural materials.\xa0Crystals, stones, and everything else organic are great reminders of natural beauty, and in my time working with them, I have found my passion! I love creating unique and one of a kind pieces and would love the chance to share my passion and positive energy with the world.  Utilizing art and construction techniques combined with methods I naturally discovered, I believe my style will quickly find its own place in the jewelry and fashion market. \xa0


Citrine Pendant, Amethyst Hamsa Ring, Lemurian Quartz Ring, and Kyanite Pendant.





My fiance and I are so devoted to this endeavor that we have planned a move to Colorado in August, near the Rocky Mountains. Living there, I will have access to material sources that would otherwise be unavailable, for either no or very reduced costs.


Jasper, Howlite, and Quartzite with Turtle.



With my own resources, I have been able to create a number of pieces that have already sold.  However, I am currently unable to launch a comprehensive site due to a lack of tools and supplies.  With the help of the Kickstarter community, I know I will have the materials to create and maintain a variety of products to stock the site with.


Garnet, Tiger's Eye, Onyx, and Hamsa.



All pieces that I create are one of a kind, utilizing the natural color and form of crystals. \xa0Even replicated, each piece from bracelet to pendant reflects the individuality of the stones themselves. \xa0As of now, I am able to create pieces using mostly Amethyst, Quartz, Citrine, and Kyanite. With the funds raised by pledges, the possibilities will be endless! \xa0I intend to use those funds to purchase high quality wire for wrapping and embellishing, as well as raw crystals, beads, cording and tools. \xa0In addition, I would like to acquire a rock tumbler, allowing me to gather my own raw crystals to use for jewelry. \xa0In doing so, I will cut down on the cost of construction, resulting in lower product prices and a higher chance of success. \xa0Raw crystals that I gather myself but do not use for construction can be sold in bulk.


Smoky Quartz. Amethyst, Brass, and Quartz Pendants.




Available products will be Rings, Bracelets, Necklaces, Pendants, Accessory Clips, Loc Wraps, Pet Collars and Collar Clips.Products will be shipped worldwide and posted by the next day.Each product will come in an eco-friendly box with a unique, hand-written scroll detailing information on the stones used.


Citrine and Amethyst Pet Collars with Suede Cording.





With the funds raised by pledges, I hope to create a self-sustaining creation machine! \xa0But that's not the end! \xa0If successful, I will be able to eventually branch into hair clips and headbands, home decor, and more!Reward Time!If I am able to reach my goal, supporters will have the chance to choose from a selection of crystals and minerals for their gift. \xa0If you don't have a material preference, you can tell me you favorite color, season, or style of clothing. \xa0I very much look forward to creating the gifts for my supporters!


Terminated Clear Quartz and Lapis Lazuli Wire Ring.








Imperial, Chinese, and Fancy Jasper Accessory Clip."]

blurb: Our nighttime flag football kit has fiber-optics and interactive LED technologies to light players, football, flags and the field.
name: Catch the Night with Flag Football AfterDark
story:
["StoryWe love flag football!From informal fun in the park with friends, throwing the ball around with the kids in the backyard or competitive league play on the weekends, we can't get enough.\xa0But flag football hasn't changed since it's was first played in the 1940's.We want to transform the game for both backyard enthusiasts and serious flag footballers\xa0with wearable fiber-optics and interactive LED technology.Our innovative, lighted uniforms and equipment means that playing time is no longer limited by daylight or the cost and hassle of finding a lit field.\xa0We have a modern take on traditional flag football — and want to move it beyond how it’s been played for the last 75 years — with the AfterDark Flag Football Kit.


AfterDark Technologies Flag Football Gear






Can't find time during the day for your favorite sports?

Don't want the hassle and expense of renting a lighted field?

Looking for a new experience for your teams or your children?

AfterDark Flag Football lets players interact in the dark using fiber-optic jerseys that light the players and flags, LED cones to define the field and end-zones, and an LED-powered football. Interactive technology provides a visual rush countdown on the quarterback’s jersey, eliminating inconsistent “one-Mississippi, two-Mississippi” counts. And all of it comes packaged in a convenient carryall, for easy travel and storage. 
The AfterDark Flag Football ExperienceFor six months, we’ve field-tested our gear with some of the largest flag football leagues in both the U.S. and Europe — hosting live games using AfterDark. We’ve incorporated feedback into the final product design and have been overwhelmed with the incredible response to the AfterDark Flag Football experience. 


The AfterDark Flag Football Experience





We are proud to work with so many enthusiastic flag fans including adult social teams such as Social Boston Sports, Texas Sports and Social Club, and Santa Monica Beach Flag Football; intramural teams including Babson College and Assumption College, and children's leagues including New England Flag Football — an NFL Flag league for 5-14 year olds. AfterDark’s Flag Football Kit has also been tested with flag football leagues across England and Scotland, in partnership with Pulling the Flag. 




AfterDark testers include some of the biggest flag football leagues in the U.S. and Europe





About the AfterDark Flag Football KitFor Kickstarter, we would like to thank pledges with kits for two players (1v1) up to full teams of fourteen players (7v7).\xa0Each kit contains:
Fiber-optic jerseys that light the player and the flags (Each jersey can be easily switched between six colors and comes with a pair of flags)
LED cones to define the field and end-zones\xa0
An LED-powered football\xa0
A travel bag for easy travel and storage\xa0
A spare jersey for referees in 5v5 kits and upwards
-\xa0Basically\xa0everything you need to play flag football AfterDark!







Quarterback Visual Rush CountdownThe AfterDark Flag Football Kit replaces the inconsistent “one-Mississippi, two-Mississippi” quarterback countdowns with an interactive LED in each jersey. Simply press the quarterback countdown button, then take the hike and the quarterback’s jersey counts down visually with alternating colors.















Perfect for Children Ages Six and UpAnd the best part? AfterDark Flag Football is not just for adult leagues and intramurals. It’s also designed for children ages six and up. Whether it’s an official league game or a fun scrimmage, you can play on beaches, parks, campsites, even in the backyard. With the sun setting earlier, extend your playing time!








Our fiber-optic and LED-powered jerseys will be available in two sizes: Youth and Adult. Each version is adjustable for a wider range of fit within each size.








So you’ve decided to back us on Kickstarter. What happens next?
We are ready to start full scale manufacturing. Our circuit boards are fully designed and tested; our supplier in California is ready to begin production. Upon successful funding via Kickstarter, the next major milestone for bringing AfterDark Flag Football gear to market is to cut injection mold tooling and produce test samples. Our mechanical engineer has identified relevant suppliers; we are ready to take our designs and make this dream a reality.








About the AfterDark Technologies Team
Each year, more than 20 million people play flag football. And we are no exception. However, life gets busy; and we would be frustrated when there weren’t enough daylight hours to get field time. We were deterred by the cost and hassle of renting lit fields and the disappointment of cutting games short when it got too dark.Our goal is to combine our love of sports and technology to create a way to play flag football anytime, without the need for a lighted field. But our idea grew beyond that — now we want to do introduce you to the AfterDark experience. We want to change the playing field — literally — with fiber-optics and LED technologies.









Daniel Wilson, Founder and CEOOur founder and CEO Dan Wilson is serial inventor across a range of industries, including high tech and medical devices. He founded AfterDark Technologies while pursuing his MBA at Babson College F.W. Olin Graduate School of Business in Wellesley, MA. He is an alumni of Babson’s incubator program, designed to accelerate the development of student entrepreneurial ventures, and is a recipient of the school’s Entrepreneurship Award, presented annually to a student demonstrating outstanding scholarship and exemplary entrepreneurial actions, leadership, and service to the Babson community. Dan was also a runner-up in The Arthur M. Blank Center Entrepreneurship B.E.T.A. Challenge in 2013 with AfterDark Technologies. He holds a B.S. in Applied Economics and Management from Cornell University.
Michael Audi, Electrical EngineerOur electrical engineer Mike Audi has years of rapid product development experience with a focus on embedded systems. His previous design work includes development of a GPS-denied Bayesian navigation system; a solar-panel feasibility device; and next-generation development for the Coca-Cola freestyle machine. His specialties include embedded control, wireless communication, sensing, android application development and circuit/PCB design. He is a recipient of the Robert H. Grant innovation award and holds B.S. degrees in Electrical and Computer Engineering along with Robotics Engineering from Worcester Polytechnic Institute.e.
Samuel Notaro, Mechanical EngineerOur mechanical engineer Sam Notaro has been a serial entrepreneur for the last four years. He has worked in the construction equipment and consumer goods fields. He holds multiple patents and has a background in plastic-injection molding. Sam is the recipient of the Stanley I. Weiss Design Award and has competed in a half-dozen innovation competitions. He received his B.S. in both Aerospace Engineering and Mechanical Engineering as well as his M.S. in Aeronautical Engineering from Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute in Troy, N.Y., in 2011. His background in engineering — coupled with his tenacious attitude and innovative thinking — makes him a perfect fit for AfterDark Technologies.
Join our team!\xa0With your support, we will bring the AfterDark experience to the millions of people that play flag football. Please support us and be part of our community. Help us change the playing field.Got a question? We're here for you.
If you have questions at any time, during or after the campaign, please ask us a question via the Kickstarter page (that way we can share it with our community), and you can always reach us at info@afterdarktechnologies.com."]

blurb: Raspberry Pi powered Nixie Tube Calculator using IN-12 Nixie Tubes.
name: Nixie Tube Calculator
story:
['StoryThe Nixie Tube Calculator is a fusion of vintage and modern technology. It’s intended to serve as much as a piece of art as it is to serve as a functional device. The calculator is available in a variety of kit forms, depending on how much existing components you have on hand, as well as a fully assembled version.


Assembled Calculator





I’ve focused on two key concepts: hackability and modularity. Hackability is achieved by using a Raspberry Pi to serve as the ‘brain’ of the clock. The Raspberry Pi is a robust inexpensive single board computer that typically runs the Linux operating system. The calculator software is written in Python and source code will be provided. Modularity is achieved by separating the project into several subassemblies. There are three keypads and two Nixie Displays modules. An I2C bus connects the keypads and displays, allowing you to easily reconfigure, delete, or add additional modules. The basic design could easily be extended to a 12-digit calculator, or a 4x2 keypad could be swapped with a 4x4 keypad to yield more functions. 


Nixie Display Boards, Front and Back View





The Nixie display modules, pictured above, feature four tubes per module. Rather than multiplexing, an individual dedicated driver chip is assigned to each tube. The drivers are then connected to I2C IO expanders, which in turn talk to the I2C bus on the Raspberry Pi. There is a provision for LED tube backlighting already designed into the driver boards, although the pictures above do not show the LED backlighting in use. It’s an option that’s there if you want it. 


Keypads





The keypads, pictured above, use Cherry MX blue key switches with custom printed keycaps. The Cherry MX blue is a quality key switch, often favored by gamers for its tactile feel and clicky sound. Key caps can easily be removed and replaced. If you don’t like the functions that I have chosen for the keys, you could have your own keycaps printed.


Power Supply Board and Raspberry Pi





The final subassembly of the kit is the power supply board, pictured above next to the raspberry pi. A standard 12V wall wart is used to supply power to the power supply board, which features a 5V switching regulator to supply the pi and other electronics, as well as a high voltage switching power supply to power the Nixie Tubes. The entire kit is designed using through-hole components, making it accessible to builders who do not have the complex tools or skills that are necessary to work with SMD devices. A high-quality temperature controlled soldering iron is recommended (a $90 Hakko is a good choice). Only two IO pins on the Raspberry Pi are used for the I2C communication to the modules, leaving the vast majority of IO pins available for custom hacks should you choose to do so. 


PC-Boards





The pc-boards are all professionally designed using modern CAD software, and will be professionally manufactured using a reliable board fabricator. They will feature all the amenities of modern pcboard manufacturing, such as plating of surfaces for easy soldering, solder mask, etc. Note that although only one of each pc-board is pictured above, the kits will come with two nixie display boards and two 4x4 keypads
The case is laser-cut acrylic. For the kits, it will come as a set of flat pieces that are easily assembled using 4-40 machine screw hardware. The case currently pictured in the video and screenshots is prototype quality. The final case that is included in the kits will have a full back and bottom sections to keep fingers out of the electronics.']

blurb: A simple device that uses a calming pattern of light to help users fall asleep by training their breathing
name: The Sleep Sensei - Fall Asleep Faster Without Medication
story:
['Story
Social
Follow the project on Facebook or Twitter!
















The Device Design
The Sleep Sensei is designed to shine a pattern of light through your eyelids. This pattern of light is used to coach your breathing pattern, which encourages your breaths to become longer as time progresses. To ensure that enough light is delivered, I put four LEDs on the device; however, the maximum brightness is adjustable to allow for different user tastes. In order to cater to varying heights of nightstands, the device is able to pivot to encompass a wide range of scenarios. For those who sleep with a partner, I added side-shields to concentrate the light's focus, reducing stray light that may annoy others.







I chose laser cutting to make the kit easy to ship and mass produce. With the target order volume (around 1000 units) in mind, laser cutting proved to be an affordable way to create a custom design.The circuit board was designed with fritzing, and the logic and programming were done with arduino, which are both open source tools.All aspects of the design (arduino code, circuit board designs, mechanical design files, website assets, photos, and documentation)\xa0are open source and are available for download on my github page. I will continue to refine the design and produce more prototypes using the Kickstarter funding, and during the development time, I encourage advanced users to fork the repository and provide me with suggestions and ideas to include in the final product!Why Red Light?
The Sleep Sensei uses light to help you fall asleep, so I wanted to make sure that the light reduces any negative impacts that late-night light can have. Blue/white light actually keeps you awake, while green light has a similar effect and can\xa0suppress your melatonin output. This leaves red light, which "has the least power to shift circadian rhythm and suppress melatonin." It's recommended to adjust the Sleep Sensei's brightness such that you can just barely see it through your eyelids, ensuring that the intensity is low enough to avoid any negative effects.How it WorksThe Sleep Sensei works by reducing your breathing rate, causing increased relaxation and bringing your breathing pattern closer to the reduced breathing pace that is typical of sleep. It also has the \xa0benefit of giving you something to focus on for an extended period of time, which can be helpful for those with sleep issues due to active minds.







Using calming red light, the Sleep Sensei produces a sine wave pattern of light that you follow with your\xa0breathing.\xa0As the light begins to brighten, the user inhales, and as the light dims, the user exhales. As time passes, the breath length increases up to the maximum length specified by the user’s settings. It is a very gradual and unnoticeable change that happens progressively over time.Who it's forThe Sleep Sensei primarily helps those with sleeping problems caused by stress or an overactive mind at bedtime. The current design of the Sleep Sensei is primarily designed for users that can lie on their side or stomach to fall asleep; however, if you prefer to fall asleep on your back for medical or other reasons, you can still use the Sleep Sensei on an elevated surface to point down towards your eyes.
Features
Bright and Directable LightThe main innovation of the Sleep Sensei is its use of bright light that is capable of being seen through the eyelids in order to make it visible with the user's eyes closed. Other similar products are just not bright enough to achieve this and require open eyes.The Sleep Sensei has a pivoting base which allows you to shine the coaching light directly at the eyelids no matter how tall, short, or non-existent your nightstand is.Adjustable BrightnessThe maximum brightness of the Sleep Sensei can be adjusted at any time using the adjustment wheel. This allows you to shine the Sensei's light on a wall for eyes-open coaching, dim it a bit if you are sensitive to light, or stare right at it for a meditation session.Customizable Breathing PatternAnother unique innovation of the Sleep Sensei is the user's ability to program custom breath lengths to suit their preferences and breathing rates. The user can choose initial and final breaths ranging from four to 20 seconds in duration. Defaults are available as a starting point.Simple DesignWhen I set out to make this project, I was determined to make the final design as simple as possible to keep the price low and to make using the Sleep Sensei simple and easy.Feedback and the Sleep Study\xa0When I first created the Sleep Sensei, I used it on myself for several weeks resulting in a general feeling that it was helping me to fall asleep faster. I wanted to quantify this somehow, so I began tracking my sleep using a sleep tracking app on my smartphone. After seeing a significant positive trend in the amount of time it took me to fall asleep using the Sleep Sensei, I decided that I wanted data from more users to see if the device worked for others. Thus I started the Sleep Study.\xa0The hypothesis was simple: “The Sleep Sensei will reduce users’ average time to fall asleep.” I made posts on reddit’s /r/insomnia, /r/arduino, and /r/quantifiedself subreddits asking for volunteers for the study using this advertisement \xa0(The device was initially named the Sleep Coach). Of the five volunteers who replied to the advertisement and participated, all of them showed some improvement in the time it took them to fall asleep. The full report can be found here, and the raw data from the study can be found here.\xa0Some comments from the study participants:\xa0“I think the quality of sleep has been improving, and I think that’s the Sleep Sensei. When I start having issues again I pull it out and it does help” – Alice S, TX\xa0“I was really impressed with the Sleep Sensei- it cut the amount of time it took me to fall asleep by about half … based on the survey, I basically don’t have insomnia anymore and it feels that way”\xa0Marijke S, MA“The Sleep Sensei allows me to fall asleep in at least under 30 minutes, sometimes even as few as 7 minutes, which is great for me! I would definitely recommend this device to anyone who is on the search for something new to help them fall asleep, someone who perhaps has tried every other sleep aid without finding anything that truly helps yet. The Sleep Sensei is awesome!” – Kate B, GA\xa0“I’ve noticed a HUGE decrease in how long it takes me to fall asleep which has been wonderful! I really like the machine.  It’s easy to use and works well.” – Kelly P, LA\xa0Now I want to reach a much wider audience with the Sleep Sensei by launching this Kickstarter. Hopefully it will help others as much as it helped the study participants!Featured by:















The Sleep Sensei Story

\xa0I have trouble falling asleep at night. I used to take over-the-counter remedies, and I've tried prescription stuff, but these either made me feel groggy the next day or had side effects that were not worth the benefits. I then stumbled upon some smartphone apps and devices that use a rising and falling pattern of light to help you fall sleep by training your breathing. I tried these with some success, but I found that they all had one major flaw: they required your eyes to be open. Who in the world tries to fall asleep with their eyes open?!

Using my arduino skills, I set out to create a device that will help coach my breathing to ease myself to sleep with my eyes closed. Thus the Sleep Sensei was born, with its pivoting base and four ultra-bright red LEDs that can shine through eyelids, it was created to address the problems of similar apps and devices.Choosing the Kickstarter GoalWhen I first started producing Sleep Sensei for the sleep study, I created a simple design that I could manufacture cheaply using parts from my local hardware store. Each one was made by hand, a process that took about 90 minutes per Sleep Sensei (longer if I had to troubleshoot a problem with my low-quality homemade circuit boards).After receiving such positive feedback from the sleep study, I wanted to bring the Sleep Sensei to the masses, but I knew I couldn’t continue spending hours just to produce a dozen devices. Thus I have turned to outsourcing the circuit board manufacture and assembly as well as making the mechanical components by laser cutting. I secured multiple quotes and found that I need to produce at least 1000 Sleep Senseis in order to make them economically viable. For example, a batch of 100 circuit boards costs over four times more per board than a batch of 1000 boards!The TimelineAssuming the Kickstarter is fully funded, this is the plan to make Sleep Sensei a reality:







Progress







Rewards Photos and DetailsNote: the Sleep Sensei is still under development, so the images below will differ from the final product.The bare board:







Just the board. Provide your own electrical components and soldering skills to complete the board, or just hang it on your keychain as a token of appreciation for helping this project become a reality.The Sleep Sensei Kit:









Includes laser-cut parts, assembled electronics board, battery pack (2 AA batteries not included), hinge hardware, and all other necessary hardware (TBD). It should take less than 5 minutes to assemble and will include easy to follow instructions.The Assembled Sleep Sensei:







The completed Sleep Sensei fully assembled by yours truly.Logo designed by RMRDesign']

blurb: A fictional story of the supernatural with fresh atmospheres, magic and plot twists.
name: Pretty Like A Devil by LM Ballinger
story: ['StoryEzra Haywood didn’t like the idea of returning to Shallow Creek again but his sister knew it would be the best place to hide. Attempting to live a somewhat normal life he goes back to school and meets the very beautiful Tuesday Robert’s, who falls in love with him nearly instantly, although he refuses to get close to her. If she found out what he was, he’d never forgive himself. Every person he had fallen in love with over the last 128 years had either been killed or used as leverage against him. He couldn’t have that happen again.After finding success in his distance and pushing her away, Tuesday gets thrown deep into the world that Ezra and his sister live in and he has no choice but to intervene.Will he run? Will he fight for her? Will he tell her what he is? Vampires were never meant to love humans.']

blurb: Completely 100% natural noncomedogenic make up for every skin type.  So good for you you can even eat it!
name: Blushing Roses Cosmetics
story: ["StoryI am creating all natural cosmetics suitable for everyone. \xa0Everything from foundation to eyeliner and blush. \xa0I will be using plants and foods in powdered form to get varying color pigments. \xa0Only the best ingredients for your skin will be used. \xa0Some ingredients are aloe vera, shea butter, collagen, cocoa, and glycerin. \xa0Everything will be 100% safe for human consumption as well. \xa0If you wouldn't want something in your body....why put it on your face?!"]

blurb: Creating a neighborhood portable library for kids 1 and Up!
name: Little Free Kids Library
story: ["StoryMy 3yr old and 5yr old love books and they LOVE to hear stories! My son is an avid fan of dinosaurs and monsters and my daughter's favorite book is The Giving Tree...so we decided to give our neighborhood a community makeover by creating a Little Free Library for Kids! The Bay Area has some cool ones for adults but we never see anything for the stroller mom and families who scoot and walk through the neighborhood...this is also a fun way to connect with the neighborhoods around us."]

blurb: Chalk caters for all your laser cutting and engraving requirements. Its about showing your very own creative flare.
name: Chalk _ specialist laser cutting and engraving craft shop
story: ["StoryA few years ago my wife's aunt opened a laser cutting and engraving craft shop. It was only till a few months ago that my wife realised she had a huge passion for crafting after her aunt taught her all the techniques to use when crafting. She really does some unique and stunning pieces and I must admit, I got caught up in the craft industry as well !We would now love to have the opportunity to open our very own craft store here on the Costa Del Sol.\xa0We would love to teach others how to craft too. Its something that adults and kids would love doing!We have big dreams for our business and we hope that one day we can grow our business even more."]

blurb: Tired of scrubbing your brushes? Let PaintSoap clean them for you! It's eco-friendly, saves water and works on all water-based paints.
name: PaintSoap - Obsidian Standard
story:
["StoryIntroducing PaintSoap

PaintSoap, was invented by a teacher who was tired of cleaning her paint brushes by hand or with harsh chemicals. She took many months to test, retest and find the perfect combination of environmentally safe ingredients that will help keep your brushes clean and reusable.\xa0The formula is safe and easy to use. All that you need to do is just add PaintSoap to about half a gallon of water, stir with the brush and let it soak for about 5 minutes. It's also quite entertaining to watch as well, which is an added bonus. 


We're a team of do-it-yourselfers with a dream of getting this product into the hands of everyone that wants a fast, safe, and eco-friendly option for taking care of the worst part of painting... the clean-up. Please donate and help us get this product to the world.\xa0Latex, Acryilic, or any water-based paintWhether you're painting a craft project with acrylics or remodeling a room, PaintSoap will help you clean your brushes so you can use them time and time again as if they were new.\xa0


Giving Back1% of each PaintSoap purchase will help bring clean water access to communities in need. Check out more on our website http://www.obsidianstandard.comPaintSoap will be manufactured/packaged in America.\xa0Thank you."]

blurb: Help the  RISD '15 Sculpture Graduate Students fund a show at Flux Factory in NYC curated by artist and RISD Professor, Anthony Graves.
name: Cement All at Flux Factory, NYC
story: ['StoryThe Rhode Island School of Design Sculpture MFA class of 2015 organized a group show, Cement All, at the Flux Factory in Long Island City, curated by NYC-based artist, curator, and RISD professor Anthony Graves. \xa0(The Show Opens July 9th, 2015 and runs through July 12th, 2015 with opening and closing receptions) This fundraiser will help us make the show an extra success; the majority will be used to publish a catalogue of texts and images dealing with the limits of materiality, the modern condition, and its conceptual framework. It will also take the financial burden off of 8 emerging artists and allow us to install the best show possible!\xa0Cement All at Flux Factory will provide an opportunity for the recent sculpture graduates to establish a fruitful, critical dialogue with like-minded artists and writers. This event will establish an arena for creative and critical dialogue between contemporary artists and writers.\xa0In addition, we will create a catalogue with documentation of the work and accompanying text from New York based poets and writers, Christine Kelly and Douglas Ross.\xa0Funding for this exhibition and catalogue is essential to further advance our unique expertise as a united group, as contemporary artists, and as recent RISD graduates.']
